subject: openpower:dreport: add guarded resolved and ephemeral records to BMC dump
commitMessage:
openpower:dreport: add guarded resolved and ephemeral records to BMC dump

1) Append GUARD blob to the dump
2) List guard records, resolved records and ephemeral records
and write to guard.log file
3) Append guard.log file to the dump

Tested:
root@ever8bmc:/tmp/test/obmcdump_00000000_1648632722# ls -lah GUARD
-r--r-----    1 root     root       20.0K Mar 30 09:32 GUARD
root@ever8bmc:/tmp/test/obmcdump_00000000_1648632722#

guard tool return error message if some failure, please include error message too like I mentioned some other patch.

For example, -e is not supported now so we need to see the error but, looks commit message didn't show that? I am missing missing something?

https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/blob/master/tools/dreport.d/include.d/functions#L16

If the command fails we are logging error as shown above if we want to capture stderr in the output file we need to modify that and it will affect all the places it is used

root@p10bmc:~# guard -l 2>&1 > /tmp/tmp
root@p10bmc:~# cat /tmp/tmp 
No unresolved records to display

@ojayanth can i modify the add_cmd_output to write the error returned from the command to the log file? Do you see any impact
This is good to have , since dd_cmd_output is common api and consumed by different plugin you should tested it properly. Better to get diffrent commit for this enhancement.
Ack

Thanks for pushing the plugin to capture the guard records.

I am ok to push a new patch to include error messages if the given command failed to execute or to capture the error message that was added by the command.

this path is working if there is a change we will change it.
